# Global Land Temperature Analysis

A comprehensive data analysis project examining global land temperature patterns, identifying the hottest and coldest countries, and visualizing temperature trends over time using Python.

## 📊 Overview

This project analyzes historical land temperature data to uncover patterns and relationships between temperature, geographic location (latitude/longitude), and temporal trends. The analysis includes statistical summaries, correlation studies, and interactive visualizations.

## 🚀 Features

- **Data Cleaning & Preprocessing**: Automated handling of missing values, data type conversion, and date formatting
- **Statistical Analysis**: Comprehensive descriptive statistics using scipy.stats
- **Geographic Pattern Detection**: Identification of top 10 hottest and coldest countries
- **Temporal Analysis**: Time-series visualization of global temperature evolution
- **Correlation Studies**: Heatmap analysis of relationships between temperature, latitude, and longitude
- **Interactive Visualizations**: Plotly-based interactive time series charts

